{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68975a8e-aa27-4657-b350-e59560070bde","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit is the only one where the skip reason is a **named property** on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89590fec-6aa5-43c6-b2b8-fcd1eb0f8028","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"481A:246DE:313AD9B:35F77E9:69FBE704"},"id":"a3b07607-bf9a-49db-8008-a4183e4f2159","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:12:42.442Z","parentId":"2fd63ceb-4244-4ed0-baed-c9ed6d3c5de1"}
